.TH "calc_nnode_num" 9 "calc_nnode_num" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calc_nnode_num \- calculate nnode number.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" calc_nnode_num
.BI "(int row "  ","
.BI "int col "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "row" 12
the row in the tree (root is zero)
.IP "col" 12
the column in the row (leftmost is zero)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The nnode number is a number that uniquely identifies a nnode and can be used
easily to traverse the tree from the root to that nnode.

This function calculates and returns the nnode number for the nnode at \fIrow\fP
and \fIcol\fP.
